An anti-drug abuse crusader has urged churches to train people on handling gender violence cases.Gladys Chania also urged clerics to teach couples how to avoid violence at home. She said churches play a huge role in shaping the society and people s perceptions. Chania spoke at Uplands village, Lari constituency, on Monday. The church invites experts to train on different topics during seminars. They can also extend the training to cover gender violence, she said.Chania said leaders should help churches organise seminars, especially in rural areas where many people are illiterate and are not familiar with conflict resolution.Chania, who was the Kiambu county TNA coordinator, will run for woman representative.